# Protos-Web

Live: https://www.protosweb.eu · Repo: ProtosEschatos/Protos-Web · Supabase: `laqnnzavwbojntfiqmxj`

## Stack

Next.js 16 App Router · React 19 · TypeScript · Tailwind · next-intl · **Supabase (sole backend)** · Vercel.

**Not Convex** — ignore Convex plugin rules; this project does not use Convex.

## Before you work

1. Secrets placement: `docs/security.md` — `ADMIN_SECRET` on Vercel only, never Supabase.
2. Admin UI: `docs/admin-console.md`
3. Full memory: Protos-Agent GitHub `memory/projects/protos-web.md`
4. Architecture: `docs/architecture.md`

## Deploy

- **GitHub only:** `git push origin main` → Vercel production auto-deploy
- **Never** Vercel CLI (`vercel deploy`, etc.)
- Supabase migrations: `supabase/migrations/` → GitHub Actions `supabase-db-push.yml` (`supabase db push`)
- Edge functions: `supabase-deploy-functions.yml` on `supabase/functions/**`
- Commit only when the user asks

## Supabase clients

- Public reads: `src/lib/supabase.ts` singleton + `src/lib/supabase/env.ts`
- Admin writes: `src/lib/supabase-admin.ts` (service role)
- Do not add duplicate Supabase client wrappers

## Agent memory

- Source: GitHub `ProtosEschatos/Protos-Agent` only (`src/lib/agent-memory.ts`)
- Private repo needs `GITHUB_TOKEN` on Vercel
- Never hardcode machine filesystem paths

## Env files

- Do not touch `.env*` unless the user explicitly asks
- Canonical secret map: `docs/security.md` only — no duplicate env tables in docs

## Features

- **Fix, don't remove** user-facing features (3D showcase, backgrounds, nav) without explicit user approval
- Showcase `/portfolio-showcase`: no Header/Footer/SiteBackground; phases `loading` | `intro` | `playing`
- DOM = UI chrome; Canvas = 3D only (`src/components/three/**`)
- Minimize diff scope; match existing style and CSS variables
- Croatian copy for admin-facing strings

## Verify

`npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm run build` before push.
